        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 6:43PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Miles City, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Miles City, Matthews Recreation Area and Strawberry Hill
Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
